# Package Boundaries

## Never import across boundaries

Packages under `packages/` must never import from `scripts/` or repo-root modules. If shared logic is needed, move it to `momentum_core` or the owning domain package.

## Dependency DAG (must not be violated)

```
momentum_core        (no heavy deps -- no torch, no alpaca-py)
  <- momentum_env    (gymnasium, numpy, pandas)
  <- momentum_agent  (torch, momentum_env, momentum_core)
  <- momentum_train  (torch, momentum_agent, momentum_env, momentum_core)
  <- momentum_live   (alpaca-py, momentum_agent, momentum_env, momentum_core)
```

## Consolidation pattern

When two packages need the same utility, move it to `momentum_core` and re-export from the domain package for backward compatibility:

```python
# momentum_core/data.py  -- canonical implementation
# momentum_train/data.py  -- re-export
from momentum_core.data import DataManager
__all__ = ["DataManager"]
```

## momentum_core stays lightweight

No `torch`, `alpaca-py`, `gymnasium`, or other heavy deps. Only stdlib + minimal packages.
